It is the perfect supply line and the last one you should ever use: the ofrendas travel to the villages and the sierras through the one week the army will not stop a procession, and among the marigolds and the copal go the things the columns need, wrapped in the cloth that covered someone's grandmother's photograph. It reaches the sierra. It always reaches the sierra. And then the campesinos who built the altar for their own dead learn what was hidden among their flowers, and something between them and the Movement breaks that no dotación will mend — because you asked the dead to carry guns, and in the villages the dead are not a figure of speech.
